00:18:26,356 --> 00:18:30,360
-Wow, that's dirty.
-Yeah.

242
00:18:34,031 --> 00:18:35,490
Hey, kids.

243
00:18:37,326 --> 00:18:40,787
He doesn't have to spend
the whole evening with me...

244
00:18:41,038 --> 00:18:42,789
... but at least check in.

245
00:18:44,208 --> 00:18:46,126
There you are!

246
00:18:47,711 --> 00:18:50,297
You got away from me.

247
00:18:50,589 --> 00:18:54,676
-But you found me.
-Here, Ross, take our picture.

248
00:18:54,885 --> 00:18:58,263
Smile. You' re on Janice Camera.

249
00:18:59,056 --> 00:19:00,807
Kill me. Kill me now.

250
00:19:05,812 --> 00:19:08,524
Hi, l' m Rachel.

251
00:19:08,732 --> 00:19:11,193
So whose friend are you?

252
00:19:14,655 --> 00:19:18,200
Look at me, spilling everywhere.

253
00:19:19,993 --> 00:19:21,787
Everybody, it's Fun Bobby!

254
00:19:25,123 --> 00:19:28,585
Hey, sorry I'm late.
But my grandfather...

255
00:19:28,752 --> 00:19:30,587
...died about two hours ago.

256
00:19:30,796 --> 00:19:36,468
But I couldn't get a flight
out till tomorrow, so here I am.

257
00:19:36,927 --> 00:19:42,432
Hey, Fun Bobby! How's it going, man?
Whoa! Who died?

258
00:19:46,687 --> 00:19:49,606
It's gonna be an open casket,
you know?

259
00:19:50,774 --> 00:19:53,610
So at least I'll get to see him again.

260
00:19:57,781 --> 00:20:00,951
Bobby? Fun Bobby?

261
00:20:01,994 --> 00:20:04,413
Let me talk to you for just a sec.

262
00:20:04,830 --> 00:20:07,374
I recently lost
a grandparent myself...

263
00:20:07,583 --> 00:20:10,586
...so I really know exactly
how you feel.

264
00:20:10,794 --> 00:20:13,797
But you' re really bringing
the party down.

265
00:20:15,007 --> 00:20:17,301
-l' m sorry.
-Yeah, yeah, okay.

266
00:20:18,635 --> 00:20:20,679
There you go. There you go.

267
00:20:21,930 --> 00:20:26,810
I' m gonna blow this one up
and write " Reunited " in glitter.

268
00:20:27,019 --> 00:20:28,979
All right, Janice, that's it!

269
00:20:29,146 --> 00:20:31,773
Janice. Janice.

270
00:20:31,982 --> 00:20:36,695
Hey, Janice, when I invited you,
I didn't think it meant

271
00:20:36,987 --> 00:20:39,198
Oh, no!

272
00:20:43,285 --> 00:20:45,662
I' m sorry you misunderstood.

273
00:20:46,038 --> 00:20:48,290
You listen to me!
You listen to me!

274
00:20:48,499 --> 00:20:53,295
One of these times, it's just gonna be
your last chance with me!

275
00:20:55,214 --> 00:20:57,174
Will you give me the thing?

276
00:21:00,844 --> 00:21:03,263
-Hi, Max.
-Yoko.

277
00:21:08,352 --> 00:21:11,647
I've decided to go to Minsk
without you.

278
00:21:12,689 --> 00:21:15,484
-Wow.
-lt won't be the same...

279
00:21:16,318 --> 00:21:19,988
... but it will still be Minsk.
Happy New Year.

280
00:21:21,573 --> 00:21:25,327
-Are you all right?
-Yeah, l' m fine. I' m fine.

281
00:21:30,707 --> 00:21:32,251
Come on.

282
00:21:34,253 --> 00:21:38,507
-You' re going to Minsk.
-No, l' m not going to Minsk.

283
00:21:38,715 --> 00:21:40,384
You are so going to Minsk.

284
00:21:40,676 --> 00:21:44,555
You belong in Minsk.
You can't stay here just for me.

285
00:21:44,763 --> 00:21:47,474
If I go, I have to break up with you.

286
00:21:47,683 --> 00:21:50,686
-And I can't break up with you.
-Yes, you can.

287
00:21:50,894 --> 00:21:55,232
Just say, " Phoebe, I love you,
but my work is my life.

288
00:21:55,524 --> 00:21:57,192
That's what I have to do. "

289
00:21:57,401 --> 00:22:01,113
And I say, "Your work?
How can you say that? "

290
00:22:02,406 --> 00:22:07,619
Then you say, " I have no choice.
Can't you understand that? "

291
00:22:07,828 --> 00:22:11,874
And I say, " No! No!
I can't understand that! "

292
00:22:12,082 --> 00:22:13,667
-Ow.
-Sorry.

293
00:22:15,377 --> 00:22:18,088
And then you put
your arms around me.

294
00:22:18,505 --> 00:22:21,884
-Then you put your arms around me.
-Oh, sorry.

295
00:22:22,676 --> 00:22:27,222
And then you tell me you love me
and you'll never forget me.

296
00:22:27,431 --> 00:22:29,725
I'll never forget you.

297
00:22:31,143 --> 00:22:33,812
Then you say that you have to go...

298
00:22:34,021 --> 00:22:38,817
... because you don't wanna start the
year with me if you can't finish it.

299
00:22:45,199 --> 00:22:48,785
I' m gonna miss you,
you scientist guy.

300
00:22:51,246 --> 00:22:53,207
Hi, Dick Clark in Times Square.

301
00:22:53,457 --> 00:22:58,253
We're in a virtual snowstorm
of confetti here in Times Square.

302
00:22:58,545 --> 00:23:00,255
It gets better every....

303
00:23:00,506 --> 00:23:02,591
Here you go, kids.

304
00:23:02,799 --> 00:23:05,636
And then the peacock bit me.

305
00:23:06,470 --> 00:23:08,305
Please kiss me at midnight!

306
00:23:13,477 --> 00:23:16,939
-You seen Sandy?
-I don't know how to tell you this...

307
00:23:17,189 --> 00:23:21,443
... but she's in the bedroom
getting it on with Max.

308
00:23:21,652 --> 00:23:23,987
Oh, I did know how to tell you.

309
00:23:25,113 --> 00:23:28,784
-Hey, everybody, the ball is dropping.
-What?

310
00:23:29,701 --> 00:23:32,704
The ball is dropping!

311
00:23:34,122 --> 00:23:36,708
In 20 seconds, it'll be midnight.

312
00:23:36,917 --> 00:23:39,628
And the moment of joy is upon us.

313
00:23:40,212 --> 00:23:43,131
Looks like that no-date pact
worked out.

314
00:23:43,590 --> 00:23:46,051
Everybody looks so happy.
I hate that!

315
00:23:46,260 --> 00:23:48,554
Not everybody is happy. Hey, Bobby!

316
00:23:48,804 --> 00:23:51,473
four, three, two...

317
00:23:51,682 --> 00:23:54,476
...one! Happy New Year!

318
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:59,815
I thought I'd throw this out.
I' m no math whiz...

319
00:24:00,023 --> 00:24:05,112
... but I do believe there are
three girls and three guys right here.

320
00:24:06,321 --> 00:24:09,074
I don't feel like kissing
anyone tonight.

321
00:24:09,366 --> 00:24:13,162
-I can't kiss anyone.
-So, I'm kissing everyone?

322
00:24:13,871 --> 00:24:17,124
No, you can't kiss Ross.
That's your brother.

323
00:24:17,332 --> 00:24:19,918
So now everybody's
getting kissed but me.

324
00:24:20,127 --> 00:24:21,336
Somebody kiss me.

325
00:24:21,545 --> 00:24:25,340
Somebody kiss me! It's midnight!
Somebody kiss me!

326
00:24:25,591 --> 00:24:27,509
All right! All right!

327
00:24:28,093 --> 00:24:29,511
There!

328
00:24:35,934 --> 00:24:38,520
I wanted this to work so much.

329
00:24:39,188 --> 00:24:40,898
I'm still in there.

330
00:24:41,148 --> 00:24:44,193
Changing his diapers.
Picking his fleas.

331
00:24:44,776 --> 00:24:47,196
But he's just phoning it in.

332
00:24:48,947 --> 00:24:54,161
It's hard that something you love
so much doesn't love you back.

333
00:24:54,369 --> 00:24:57,456
I think that bitch cracked my tooth.

